China correspondent Stephen McDonell State news agency Xinhua showed images of residents outside their apartment buildings after the quake and said 6 , 000 troops and police were being dispatched to the area . It quoted a resident in the provincial capital Chengdu , who was on the 13th floor when the quake hit , as saying he felt the shaking for about 20 seconds and saw tiles fall off nearby buildings . In downtown Chongqing , Xinhua quoted a resident said : " I saw the lamps were swaying and water in my fishbowl stirring .